Privileged mode is the exception. The “reason” column explains the reason for running the containers in a particular Pod with the root user. When the main process in the container does not run as root, the UID is either 1999 default or the value configured through installer command line or install.properties. See the Installation guide for details on how to change the default UID/GID for a Suite (+CDF) installation.
</p>
